  "prompt": "How much does it cost to register a trademark in the U.S.?",
  "response": "The cost to register a trademark in the U.S. depends on the filing method and type of application:\n\n1. Online TEAS (Trademark Electronic Application System) Basic Application:\n- $250 per class of goods/services\n\n2. TEAS Plus Application:\n- $250 per class of goods/services\n- Requires more specific requirements and limitations\n\n3. TEAS Standard Application:\n- $350 per class of goods/services\n- More flexible than TEAS Plus\n\nAdditional potential costs include:\n- Legal fees if using an attorney\n- Renewal fees every 10 years\n- Maintenance documents\n\nThese fees are paid to the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) and cover the initial registration process.",
